Python:

n=int(input())
s=0
for i in range(1,n):
    if(n%i==0):
        s=s+i
if(s==n):
    print("perfect")
else:
    print("no")
----------------------------------------------
Cpp:

#include <iostream>
using namespace std;
int main() {
    int n,s=0;
    cin>>n;
    for(int i=1;i<n;i++){
        if(n%i==0){
            s=s+i;
        }
    }
    if(s==n){
        cout<<"perfect";
    }else{
        cout<<"no";
    }

    return 0;
}
-----------------------------------------------
Input:
6
Explanation:
Divisors: 1, 2, 3 â†’ 1 + 2 + 3 = 6 

Output:
perfect
